            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κἀγὼ ἀλυπότ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἐὰν γὰρ ὑμεῖς χαρῆτε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καὶ ἐγὼ χαίρω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Oecumenius. He is not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄλυπος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", for he is in captivity and surrounded by adversaries; but the joy which he is aware is already prepared for his beloved Philippians by the return of Epaphroditus, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "lessens",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " his ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λύπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This tender interweaving of his own alleviation with the rejoicing of his readers is lost, if we refer ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀλύποτ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". to the removal of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " vexation ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of seeing the recovered one so full of longing and so uneasy",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Hofmann), which, regarded as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λύπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", would be sentimental. According to Weiss, Paul intends to say: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "still more",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄλυπος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", than I have already become in consequence of Epaphroditus’ recovery. An unsuitable idea, because the comparative necessarily presupposes a certain degree of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λύπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " still remaining. In the consciousness of this Paul has written ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀλυπότ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; if it had been otherwise, he would perhaps have used, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Php 2:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κἀγὼ εὐψυχῶ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κἀγὼ χαίρω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
